aws::graph::propositions: # Aircraft Information for Mooney M20TN N411JL
The aircraft make is MOONEY AIRPLANE COMPANY, INC.
The aircraft registration is N411JL.
The aircraft model/series is M20TN.
The aircraft category is Airplane.
The aircraft has a normal airworthiness certificate.
The aircraft serial number is 31-0096.
The aircraft has retractable tricycle landing gear.
The aircraft has 4 seats.
The aircraft's last inspection was an Annual inspection on December 2, 2011.
The aircraft's certified maximum gross weight is 3368 lbs.
The aircraft has 1 reciprocating engine.
The aircraft had 594 hours of total airframe time at the time of accident.
The aircraft has an Emergency Locator Transmitter (ELT) installed.
The Emergency Locator Transmitter (ELT) was not activated.
The engine manufacturer is CONTINENTAL MOTOR.
The engine model/series is TSIO-550-G1.
The engine is rated at 280 Horsepower.
The registered owner of the aircraft is 4TH WAVE INC.
The operator of the aircraft is 4TH WAVE INC.
The operator does not hold any operating certificates.
The slowest groundspeed during the flight was below 50 knots.
The slowest groundspeed occurred at about 0902 and again at 0904.
The flight stabilized around 0906.
The flight descended from about 3,800 feet pressure altitude to 1,400 feet pressure altitude on a southerly heading.
The airspeed increased to about 130 knots before decreasing to 100 knots at the last radar return.
